```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"software": [
"anaconda/3/2021.11",
"python",
"single_index_predict_z_with_pvol.py",
"make_uniformz.py",
"single_index_predict.py",
"chunk_classifier.py",
"single_index_predict_resume.py",
"single_index_predict_f.py",
"single_index_predict_z.py",
"single_index_predict_snr.py",
"create_ppdot_all.py"
],
"resources": {
"nodes": 1,
"tasks_per_node": 1,
"cores_per_task": 1,
"gpu": 1,
"time": "20:00:00",
"memory": "50GB",
"environment": "/u/atya/conda-envs/tf-gpu4"
},
"other_requirements": {
"dependency": "afterok:1585071",
"array": "13-30",
"mail_type": "END,FAIL",
"mail_user": "s6abtyag@uni-bonn.de"
}
}
```

This script is running within the **SLURM** workload manager, using several Python scripts to perform some tasks. The script requests one full node with one task and one core assigned to that task. It requires one GPU and 50 GB of memory. The script will run for a maximum of 20 hours. The script uses the Anaconda distribution (version 3/2021.11) and activates the conda environment named "tf-gpu4". It also depends on the successful completion of job ID 1585071 and runs as an array of tasks from 13 to 30. The script sends email notifications to s6abtyag@uni-bonn.de when the job ends or fails.
